AirAsia Moves to London Gatwick From Stansted Airport

-- B y   S t e v e n   R o t h w e l l
-- 
2011-07-13T00:38:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-13/airasia-moves-to-london-gatwick-from-stansted-airport-correct-.html
(Corrects headline to say moving to Gatwick.)  AirAsia X said it’s switching U.K.
flights from London’s Stansted airport to Gatwick, south of the
capital, from Oct. 24 to tap a bigger catchment area and provide
better links for onward flights to the U.S.  Stansted has also become less attractive because people who
flew there to catch European flights with local discount
carriers are being put off by a U.K. tax increase and opting to
use AirAsia X’s service to Paris instead, the long-haul unit of
Sepang, Malaysia-based  AirAsia Bhd. (AIRA)  said today.  There’s a remote chance that the airline will hold an
initial public offering this year, though it’s more likely to
take place in 2012, Chief Executive Officer Azran Osman Rani
said today at a U.K. press briefing.  AirAsia, led by CEO Tony Fernandes, is Southeast Asia’s
biggest discount airline  To contact the reporter on this story:
